# Restore Product Review Display on Menu Page

## Problem

User reports that product reviews are not displaying on menu items. Previously, after completing an order, users could leave reviews which would then appear on the menu showing:
- Review count (e.g., "1")
- Average star rating
- Review details when clicking on the product

## Root Cause

The review system is fully implemented with:
- ✅ Backend API endpoints ([reviewController.js](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/backend/controllers/reviewController.js))
- ✅ Zustand store with [loadFromAPI()](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/stores/reviewStore.js#12-28) method ([reviewStore.js](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/stores/reviewStore.js))
- ✅ UI components ([ProductCard](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/components/common/ProductCard.jsx#10-76), `ProductReviewsPage`, `RateProductModal`)
- ✅ Review submission flow in `CustomerOrdersPage`

**However**, the [MenuPage](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/pages/Product/MenuPage.jsx#6-47) component doesn't load reviews from the API when the page mounts. This means the review store has no data, so [ProductCard](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/components/common/ProductCard.jsx#10-76) displays [(0)](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/stores/reviewStore.js#29-50) reviews even when reviews exist in the database.

## Proposed Changes

### Frontend

#### [MODIFY] [MenuPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/pages/Product/MenuPage.jsx)

Add review loading on page mount:
- Import `useReviewStore` 
- Get [loadFromAPI](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/stores/reviewStore.js#12-28) function from review store
- Add `useEffect` to call [loadFromAPI()](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/stores/reviewStore.js#12-28) when page mounts
- This will fetch all reviews from the database and populate the store

This mirrors the pattern already used in [CustomerOrdersPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/pages/Order/CustomerOrdersPage.jsx) (line 18, 27-29) and [ProductReviewsPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/pages/Product/ProductReviewsPage.jsx) (line 15, 17-19).

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification

1. **Start the application**:
   - Backend: `cd backend && npm start`
   - Frontend: `cd Frontend && npm run dev`

2. **Create a test review** (if none exist):
   - Login as a customer
   - Place an order and complete payment
   - Go to "Đơn của tôi" (My Orders)
   - Click "Đánh giá" on a purchased product
   - Submit a review with rating and comment

3. **Verify review displays on menu**:
   - Navigate to "Trang chủ" (Home/Menu page)
   - Check that the reviewed product shows:
     - Star rating (e.g., ★★★★★)
     - Review count in parentheses (e.g., "(1)")
   - Click "Xem chi tiết đánh giá" button
   - Verify the review detail page shows the review with username, rating, and comment

4. **Verify multiple reviews**:
   - Add another review from a different user (or logout and create new account)
   - Check that review count increases
   - Verify average rating updates correctly
